      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 61: hasActiveCalls() only checks conferences, so a regular one-to-one call stored in calls can be missed. That allows JamiApplicationFirebase to deactivate accounts while an active or ringing non-conference call is in progress, which can break call setup or media. Check both collections before allowing background deactivation.\n\n```suggestion\n    fun hasActiveCalls(): Boolean \u003d\n        synchronized(calls) {\n            calls.values.any { it.state?.isOver \u003d\u003d false } ||\n                conferences.values.any { it.state?.isOver \u003d\u003d false }\n        }\n```",
